I may have figured out a work around for anyone asking. If there is a better place to post this please let me know. I am in the middle of testing with some friends (when they are free) and will confirm as soon as I can. For those of you that have macs and would like to play with friends who don’t then you need to go to settings and enable beta versions. Go to the properties for Civ V click on the betas tab. After this you will type in ineedlegacyaccess into the beta access code. Then you will click check code and allow the game to update to the beta version. Whatever friends you have on PC/Linux will also need to revert to this beta version. It is from 2018 and is an annoyance that you have to go that far back but should allow multiplayer access across platforms. Now this will only work for those of you who have not updated to macOS Catalina. This is a lot to do to play cross platform but if you want to continue your games I believe this is a way to make it work!
